</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31696B0FFD8AE07FF26AD68CE13FB87" box="[199,867,1085,1110]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB3C53BFFD8AE07FF26AD68CE13FB87" blockId="13.[151,1437,1049,1506]" box="[199,867,1085,1110]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="B9781929FFD8AE07FF26AD68CC31FB87" bold="true" box="[199,321,1085,1110]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Boldly patterned, with an unusually broad head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31696B0FFD8AE07FF26AD34C925FAD8" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB3C53BFFD8AE07FF26AD34C925FAD8" blockId="13.[151,1437,1049,1506]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="B9781929FFD8AE07FF26AD34CC29FBAB" bold="true" box="[199,345,1121,1146]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Description.</emphasis>
Head as wide as pronotum, crown as long as midline of pronotum. Face and dorsum shiny black; tegmina rather short, blackish brown with bold, white patches covering clavi and adjacent corium, transversely truncate on posterior margin; tegminal tips with red line connecting pale costal markings. Male as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CBEB8FFD8AE07FAFBADFFC8E5FB10" box="[1306,1429,1194,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Microsargane" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicata">
<emphasis id="B9781929FFD8AE07FAFBADFFC8E5FB10" box="[1306,1429,1194,1217]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">M. apicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but aedeagal processes more broadly spreading, tip furcating at right angles, inner branch straight and spinelike, outer branch weakly curved and parallel-margined. Length: male and female 
<quantity id="4CF468DEFFD8AE07FC19ADA7C921FAD8" box="[1016,1105,1266,1290]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="7.2">7.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
